extract:
Critical infrastructure is a term used by governments to describe assets that are essential for the functioning of a society and economy – the infrastructure. Most commonly associated with the term are facilities for:Shelter; Heating ;
Agriculture, food production and distribution;
Water supply ;
Public health ;
Transportation systems ;
Security services.
Electricity generation, transmission and distribution; 
Renewable energy, which are naturally replenished on a human timescale, such as sunlight, wind, rain, tides, waves, and geothermal heat.
Telecommunication; coordination for successful operations
Economic sector; Goods and services and financial services ;
